law.text:
A certificate of reinstatement shall include:
The name of the statutory trust at the time its right to do business in the State was forfeited;
The name that the statutory trust will use after reinstatement, which shall comply with the provisions of this article with respect to statutory trust names;
The address of the principal office of the statutory trust in the State if different from its principal office in the State at the time the right to do business in the State was forfeited; and
The name and address of the resident agent of the statutory trust.
